## FileTree Component

The `FileTree` component is a React component responsible for rendering a hierarchical file and folder structure. It allows users to navigate through directories and select individual files.

### Purpose

This component visualizes a file system-like tree structure, enabling users to browse through nested folders and files. It supports expanding and collapsing folders, and selecting files to trigger actions.

### Key Exports and Functions

- **`FileTree`**: The main component that recursively renders the tree structure.
  - **`nodes`**: An array of `TreeNode` objects representing the files and folders to display. Each node can be either a `FolderNode` or a `FileNode`.
  - **`activeKey`**: The key of the currently selected file. Used to highlight the active file in the tree.
  - **`activeFolderPath`**: The path of the currently active folder. Used to highlight the active folder in the tree.
  - **`onSelect`**: A callback function that is invoked when a file is selected. It receives the `key` of the selected file.
  - **`onFolder`**: A callback function that is invoked when a folder is clicked. It receives the `path` of the clicked folder.
  - **`depth`**: (Optional) The current depth of the node in the tree. Used for indentation.
  - **`pathPrefix`**: (Optional) A prefix to be prepended to folder paths.

- **`FolderRow`**: Renders a single folder row in the tree.
  - Manages the expanded/collapsed state of the folder.
  - Displays a folder icon and name.
  - Handles folder clicks via the `onFolder` prop.
  - Recursively renders its children using the `FileTree` component.

- **`FileRow`**: Renders a single file row in the tree.
  - Displays a file icon and name.
  - Highlights the row if its `key` matches the `activeKey`.
  - Handles file selection via the `onSelect` prop.

### Usage Example

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { FileTree, TreeNode } from './FileTree'; // Assuming FileTree is in the same directory

// Example tree data
const sampleNodes: TreeNode[] = [
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'src',
    children: [
      {
        kind: 'folder',
        name: 'components',
        children: [
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Button.tsx', key: 'src/components/Button.tsx', title: 'Button Component' },
          { kind: 'file', name: 'Card.tsx', key: 'src/components/Card.tsx', title: 'Card Component' },
        ],
      },
      { kind: 'file', name: 'index.ts', key: 'src/index.ts', title: 'Main Index File' },
    ],
  },
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'lib',
    children: [
      { kind: 'file', name: 'utils.ts', key: 'lib/utils.ts', title: 'Utility Functions' },
    ],
  },
  { kind: 'file', name: 'App.tsx', key: 'App.tsx', title: 'App Entry Point' },
];

function App() {
  const [activeKey, setActiveKey] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [activeFolderPath, setActiveFolderPath] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const handleSelectFile = (key: string) => {
    setActiveKey(key);
    setActiveFolderPath(null); // Clear active folder when a file is selected
    console.log('Selected file:', key);
  };

  const handleSelectFolder = (path: string) => {
    setActiveFolderPath(path);
    setActiveKey(null); // Clear active file when a folder is selected
    console.log('Selected folder:', path);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <h2>File Explorer</h2>
      <FileTree
        nodes={sampleNodes}
        activeKey={activeKey}
        activeFolderPath={activeFolderPath}
        onSelect={handleSelectFile}
        onFolder={handleSelectFolder}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```
